# RENSTO PROJECT RULES - MANDATORY FOR ALL WORK

**Last Updated**: October 5, 2025
**Purpose**: Prevent architectural mistakes and ensure consistency across all development

---

## 🏗️ ARCHITECTURE - NEVER DEVIATE FROM THIS

### **Domain Architecture** (MEMORIZE THIS):
```
rensto.com          → Webflow (main site, marketplace, subscriptions, all public pages)
admin.rensto.com    → Vercel (admin dashboard only)
api.rensto.com      → Vercel (ALL API endpoints: Stripe, webhooks, etc.)
portal.rensto.com   → Vercel (customer portals - planned)
```

### **Critical Rules**:
1. ⛔ **NEVER** point rensto.com DNS to Vercel - it MUST point to Webflow
2. ⛔ **NEVER** create API routes in the main rensto.com app
3. ✅ **ALWAYS** deploy API routes to api.rensto.com subdomain
4. ✅ **ALWAYS** check CLAUDE.md before making architectural decisions

---

