- Naming convention: `{TYPE}-{FUNCTION}-{VERSION}` (e.g., `STRIPE-MARKETPLACE-001`)

---

## 💳 STRIPE INTEGRATION (CORRECT APPROACH)

### **Architecture**:
1. Webflow pages (rensto.com) contain buttons
2. Buttons call `https://api.rensto.com/stripe/checkout` via JavaScript
3. API route creates Stripe session, returns checkout URL
4. User redirects to Stripe, completes payment
5. Stripe webhook sends event to `https://api.rensto.com/stripe/webhook`
6. Webhook handler triggers n8n workflows

### **Workflow**:
```
Webflow Button → api.rensto.com/stripe/checkout → Stripe Checkout
                                                           ↓
Stripe Webhook → api.rensto.com/stripe/webhook → n8n STRIPE-* workflows
```

### **Active Stripe n8n Workflows**:
- `STRIPE-MARKETPLACE-001`: Template purchases
- `STRIPE-INSTALL-001`: Installation services
- `STRIPE-READY-001`: Ready Solutions packages
- `STRIPE-SUBSCRIPTION-001`: Monthly subscriptions
- `STRIPE-CUSTOM-001`: Custom solutions projects
- `DEV-FIN-006`: Revenue sync to Airtable

